HEADWORD: Klipspringer
<hw>Klip"spring`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D., lit.,
cliff springer.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A small, graceful South
African antelope (<spn>Nanotragus oreotragus</spn>), which, like the
chamois, springs from one crag to another with great agility; -- called
also <altname>kainsi</altname>.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>klippspringer</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kloof</ent>⟦br⟧
